{
  "doc_id": "49021",
  "text": "IL-6 levels are significantly elevated in the majority of patients with sepsis and the circulating IL-6 levels have correlated with the severity of sepsis in most studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The persistently high levels of IL-6 have been associated with the development of multiple organ failure (MOF) and poor prognosis [CITATION_3] . It has been suggested that elevated IL-6 levels reflect the activation of inflammatory response in sepsis, although the exact role of IL-6 in the pathogenesis of sepsis is not clear.",
